    "In §4.4 and §4.5 we use a linear model (Equation (1)) that predicts that test accuracy and the out-of-distribution test accuracy.",
    "We estimate the parameters of this linear model based on results from all our variants of D used in §4.",
    "For all these variants, we measure the test accuracy and the number of Known and Unknown fine-tuning examples that M fits during different fine-tuning stages.",
    "This way we collect a dataset with examples of the form (Accuracy, N Kn, N Unk), which we use to fit a linear regression model.",
    "In §4.5 we discuss out-of-distribution (OOD) results."
